  <div class="content-wrap">

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>Energizing Solutions LLC (&ldquo;Energizing Solutions&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) is an IT and professional services consultancy specializing in enterprise program leadership, digital transformation, and applied observability. We are headquartered in Bothell, Washington, USA.</p>
      <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information when you visit <strong>www.energizing-solutions.com</strong> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) or contact us directly about our services.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what is reasonably necessary to respond to inquiries and improve the Site experience.</p>
      <p><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Information you provide directly:</strong></p>
      <ul class="policy-list">
        <li>Name, email address, phone number, and message content when you contact us via the contact form or email</li>
        <li>Professional context (company, role, project details) that you voluntarily share in communications</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Information collected automatically:</strong></p>
      <ul class="policy-list">
        <li>Browser type, operating system, and device type</li>
        <li>Pages visited, time on site, and referring URL</li>
        <li>IP address (used for geographic analytics only, not to identify individuals)</li>
        <li>Cookie and session data (see Section 5 below)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="policy-list">
        <li>To respond to your inquiries and provide the services or information you request</li>
        <li>To evaluate potential engagements and follow up on business conversations</li>
        <li>To understand how visitors use the Site so we can improve its content and structure</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use your personal information for automated decision-making or profiling. We do not send unsolicited marketing emails. If you contact us, we may follow up regarding our services &mdash; you can opt out of any follow-up communication at any time by replying to that effect.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>Energizing Solutions does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. Full stop.</p>
      <p>We may share limited information in the following circumstances:</p>
      <ul class="policy-list">
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Service providers:</strong> We may use third-party tools (e.g. email hosting, analytics platforms) that process data on our behalf under appropriate data processing agreements.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Legal requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law, court order, or governmental authority.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Business transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, personal data may transfer as part of that transaction, subject to equivalent privacy protections.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Cookies &amp; Analytics</h2>
      <p>This Site uses cookies and similar technologies to understand visitor behaviour and improve performance. We use Google Analytics, which collects anonymized usage data including pages visited, session duration, and geographic region. Google&rsquo;s data practices are governed by the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
      <p>You can control cookie behaviour through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect some Site functionality but will not prevent you from accessing content.</p>
      <p>We do not use cookies for advertising, retargeting, or cross-site tracking.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain contact form submissions and email correspondence for as long as reasonably necessary to respond to your inquiry or maintain a business relationship. If no engagement results from an initial contact, we generally retain that information for no more than 24 months.</p>
      <p>Anonymized analytics data may be retained indefinitely as it cannot be used to identify individuals.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
      <p>If you have reason to believe your information has been compromised through your interaction with us, please contact us immediately at the address below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
      <ul class="policy-list">
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data, subject to any legal retention obligations</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Objection:</strong> Object to how we process your data in certain circumstances</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Portability:</strong> Request your data in a portable format where technically feasible</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the details in Section 10. We will respond within 30 days. We will not discriminate against you for exercising your privacy rights.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>This Site may contain links to third-party websites, including LinkedIn, GitHub, and Facebook. These sites operate under their own privacy policies. Energizing Solutions is not responsible for the privacy practices or content of any third-party site. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any site you visit.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>For any privacy-related questions, requests, or concerns, please contact:</p>
      <div class="contact-block">
        <p><strong style="color:var(--white);font-weight:500;">Energizing Solutions LLC</strong></p>
        <p>Bothell, Washington, USA</p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:paesteves21@outlook.com">paesteves21@outlook.com</a></p>
        <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+14253548133">425-354-8133</a></p>
        <p>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/PauloE-droid" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/PauloE-droid</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, or legal requirements. When we make material changes, we will update the &ldquo;Last Updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
      <p>We recommend reviewing this page periodically. This policy was most recently updated in March 2026.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

